Text: Lebanon just rolled her eyes at the latest Reddit thread decrying the state of her infrastructure, cracking, “If I had a lira for every time I heard that!
” She whipped up some kibbeh for the crew as she recalled her attempts to fix her Wi-Fi with duct tape—“It’s as stable as our government!
” Amidst the laughter, she emphasized that despite the chaos, her garden thrived—much like her spirit.
Her friendship with France deepened over who’d host the next gourmet night while debating whose baklava is superior.
“At least our discussions aren’t as flaky as those pastries!
Ah, just another day in the souks of life.
Ah, another day of “Can you top this?
” Meanwhile, her Wi-Fi’s as reliable as a ceasefire—hence the duct tape innovation thriving in her hands.
Yet, amidst the chaos, she whipped up kibbeh for the crew, warding off any talk of calamity.
“At least our culinary skills aren’t flaky like those pastries!
” she quipped, celebrating her bond with France over whose baklava reigns supreme.
